gomodel:SYNGO_344  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099029 replaced by GO:0048787" , "Rationale: Preembedding immunogold electron microscopy (EM) on lamina I-III of L4-L6 spinal cord sections was used to study the subcellular localization of alpha_2 delta-1. Alpha_2 delta-1 was observed at the plasma membrane of presynaptic nerve terminals of DRG neurons, at the plasma membrane of postsynaptic dorsal horn neurons and also at intracellular dendritic sites (Fig 1E, F).\n\n27/4/2017 Pim\n- In discussion with the expert we have establised that PMID:20080692 (Fig.4G) shows that the Ca-channel alpha_2 delta-1 subunit may have a TM domain predicted, but that A GPI anchor provides most likely the link to the plasma membrane. We have selected the term \"anchored component of presynaptic active zone membrane (GO:0099029)\" accordingly.. Experimental description: Male Sprague Dawley rats used." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_344" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

